Observers had not been expecting the move, even though Bundesbank chief
Hans Tietmeyer has been saying lowered rates might be possible to take
pressure off the dollar, which has plummeted to postwar lows against
the German mark and Japanese yen.
The so-called repo rate was lowered from 4.85 to 4.5 percent. The repo
rate, short for securities repurchase rate, is the main lever the
Bundesbank has on money market interest rates.
